Parliament, Monday 28 October 2019 – Economics Cluster Ministers are scheduled to answer questions for oral reply at National Council of Provinces plenary sittings tomorrow and on Thursday. Both sittings are at 14.00 in the National Council of Provinces Chamber. Ministers appearing at tomorrow’s sitting of the National Council of Provinces are the Minister of Agriculture, Land Reform and Rural Development; the Minister of Environment, Forestry and Fisheries; and the Minister of Mineral Resources and Energy. Those scheduled for Thursday’s sitting are the Minister of Economics, the Minister of Trade and Industry, the Minister of Employment and Labour and the Minister of Tourism. Section 92(2) of the Constitution obliges Cabinet Members to account to Parliament for the exercise of their powers and performance of their functions and Parliament is using this opportunity to hold the Executive accountable. For the questions scheduled for the ministers appearing tomorrow, please click:
	
